<div class="govuk-panel govuk-panel--confirmation">
  <h1 class="govuk-panel__title">
    Walkthrough complete
  </h1>
  <div class="govuk-panel__body">
    You've explored the PlanX digital planning platform used by UK councils
  </div>
</div>

<p class="govuk-body-l govuk-!-margin-top-6">
  You've just experienced <a href="https://www.planx.uk/" class="govuk-link">PlanX</a> — the same platform used by 18+ councils including Lambeth, Southwark, Camden, and Buckinghamshire to create digital planning application services. In 15 to 20 minutes, you've seen what would take weeks of procurement and vendor demos.
</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l">What you've learned</h2>

<div class="ndx-takeaway-grid">
  <div class="ndx-takeaway-card">
    <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">
      Visual flow editor
    </h3>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      PlanX lets service designers build planning application flows using a drag-and-drop editor. No coding required. Each flow guides applicants through structured questions that map to planning data standards.
    </p>
    <p class="govuk-body-s" style="color: #505a5f; font-weight: 700;">
      Value: Service designers can create and update flows without developer support
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="ndx-takeaway-card">
    <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">
      Citizen-centred design
    </h3>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Applicants answer plain English questions instead of filling in complex PDF forms. The system determines the right planning permission type, collects the right documents, and routes the application correctly.
    </p>
    <p class="govuk-body-s" style="color: #505a5f; font-weight: 700;">
      Value: More complete applications submitted first time, fewer invalid submissions
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="ndx-takeaway-card">
    <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">
      Structured data
    </h3>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Every answer maps to a planning data field, producing machine-readable application data. This enables automated validation, integration with back-office systems like BOPS, and data sharing across councils.
    </p>
    <p class="govuk-body-s" style="color: #505a5f; font-weight: 700;">
      Value: Automated processing, interoperability, and consistent data quality
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="ndx-takeaway-card">
    <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">
      Open source platform
    </h3>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      PlanX is developed by <a href="https://opendigitalplanning.org/" class="govuk-link">Open Systems Lab</a> and freely available. Multiple councils share development costs and benefit from each other's improvements. The GraphQL API ensures data is accessible and integrable.
    </p>
    <p class="govuk-body-s" style="color: #505a5f; font-weight: 700;">
      Value: Zero licence costs, community-driven development, shared innovation
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Production readiness</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">
  This demo runs the same codebase used in production by multiple UK councils. For a full deployment, you'd additionally want:
</p>

